The paper deals with communication over multiple access and interference channels, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the correlation between sources, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple source symbols to choose channel inputs is a technique used in network information theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses coding schemes and performance characterization, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
